  "text": "The consumer offset commit flow in Apache Kafka travels through the following chain:\n\n1. **Client-side initiation (KafkaConsumer)**: The public API `KafkaConsumer.commitSync()` (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/KafkaConsumer.java:1039) delegates to its internal consumer implementation.\n\n2. **Internal consumer (ClassicKafkaConsumer)**: The implementation `ClassicKafkaConsumer.commitSync()` (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ClassicKafkaConsumer.java:736) invokes the coordinator's commit method.\n\n3. **Consumer coordinator (ConsumerCoordinator)**: The `ConsumerCoordinator.commitOffsetsSync()` (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerCoordinator.java:1140) method calls `sendOffsetCommitRequest()` to send an OffsetCommitRequest to the broker.\n\n4. **Broker request handling (KafkaApis)**: The broker receives and processes the request in `KafkaApis.handleOffsetCommitRequest()` (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/KafkaApis.scala:272), which delegates to the group coordinator.\n\n5. **Group coordinator interface (GroupCoordinator)**: The interface method `GroupCoordinator.commitOffsets()` (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinator.java:349) defines the contract for handling offset commits.\n\n6. **Coordinator service (GroupCoordinatorService)**: The implementation `GroupCoordinatorService.commitOffsets()` (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorService.java:1971) schedules a write operation to the appropriate coordinator shard.\n\n7. **Coordinator runtime (CoordinatorRuntime)**: The `scheduleWriteOperation()` method (coordinator-common/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/common/runtime/CoordinatorRuntime.java:2182) queues the write operation to be executed on the shard.\n\n8. **Coordinator shard (GroupCoordinatorShard)**: The shard's `commitOffset()` (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorShard.java:852) method delegates to the offset metadata manager.\n\n9. **Offset metadata management (OffsetMetadataManager)**: The `commitOffset()` method (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetMetadataManager.java:600) validates the request, processes each partition's offset, and creates coordinator records.\n\n10. **Record generation (GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers)**: For each offset commit, `GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.newOffsetCommitRecord()` (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.java:467) creates the CoordinatorRecord that will be appended to the log.\n\n11. **Log appending (CoordinatorPartitionWriter)**: Finally, `CoordinatorPartitionWriter.append()` (core/src/main/scala/kafka/coordinator/group/CoordinatorPartitionWriter.scala:139) writes the records to the __consumer_offsets topic partition.\n\nThe entire flow ensures that consumer offset commits are durably persisted to the __consumer_offsets topic in a coordinated manner, with proper batching and error handling through the CoordinatorRuntime framework."
